item.dc:creator: @Ambokile Ambokile
item.description:
@Ambokile wrote:

[quote=“JavaTC, post:12, topic:461534”][quote author=Ambokile link=topic=564479.msg4109990#msg4109990 date=1348429811]

If you want a 608 then make one. Why make a 317 load a 608?

Because not everyone’s computer can handle an actual 608+ Client + most 600+ servers are even buggier and less stable than a 317 load 600+

“most 600+ servers” doesn’t mean all of them. If there are bugs, fix them. If there are memory problems, fix them. Hence the word “make”.
[/quote]
And yet people don’t fix them, and if they do, they won’t release it. How about rather than just saying “oh u has bugs? just fix em u fukin newb coder LAWL”, you try your hand at implementing a new game engine and fixing any bugs that pop up without knowledge of what might be causing them and what needs to be fixed.[/quote]
There’s no need to be so arrogant. I spoke to you with manners and respect so I’d appreciate the same back. Most “bugs” I’ve seen in my four-or-so years of RSPS are simply mistakes, a piece of programming logic that the programmer hasn’t picked up on, and working backwards through the methods normally solves it.
